{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Recommended: Pure AppKit + SwiftUI Settings\n      Architecture: AppDelegate-driven lifecycle, NSWindow for progress, SwiftUI only for Settings view\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Full control over window lifecycle (hide/show/close without quit)\n            NSPanel for progress popup — native, lightweight, auto-dismiss\n            Proven pattern for \"agent\" apps (no Dock, no Menu Bar)\n            Easiest to handle \"relaunch = show settings\" behavior\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            More AppKit boilerplate vs pure SwiftUI\n            Two UI paradigms (AppKit windows + SwiftUI views)","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1774718119297}
